I rated the Mobile Observatory 2 app 5 stars in 2013 and am doing the same for this amazing update. It is definitely worth my money! I've tried several other star gazing/planetarium apps but I think this one is still the best. Suggestions would be to update the web page, zima.co,  to include this version and possibly make a online video tutorial for beginning or potential users to demonstrate all of it's great features.  Thanks!!!
Excellent astronomy app, with a huge array of features.

great app for the advanced amateur. the new augmented reality is fun (would be nice if it could be calibrated/offset). Edit: couldn't figure out how to get the widget working; you just have to select the location, which is great.
replyContent: Hi, there are 2 widgets now. You have to tap on the widget icon and can then drag one on the screen. Please let me know if this works. Best regards Wolfgang

content: Since update of 8/03/19 crashes repeatedly. Has anyone else had this issue?
replyContent: Hi, thanks for your feedback. May I ask you to contact me via email at mobileobservatorypro@gmail.com. I would appreciate your help with testing the update. Regards Wolfgang

content: Nice upgrade. My favorite Astronomy App

Pro: I love the new Augmented Reality feature, this is really outstanding. I had no time (and sky condition) to compare "old" and "new" app, so the score is initial. Edit: Had the chance to test it and honestly a huge improvement over v2.75

I really like the new interface and features. Much better experience on a tablet than the old version. Voice search is cool!   Unfortunately, I still have to depend on Sky Safari for getting observing lists certifications, like those offered by the Astronomical League, the Royal Astronomical Society of Canada (of which I am a member) and so on. I understand that telescope control is coming later in the year. Due to lack of space, I cannot list the details of functionality I'd like to see, so I'll send Wolfgang a PM.  In summary:  1. Ability to download custom lists in SkyTools and Sky Safari format, and also to create custom lists. 2. Ability to log observations. 3. Current search capabilities aren't bad, but there can be better cross-referencing with catalog designations (especially star catalogs). 4. Allow user to specify an obstructed horizon (degrees above horizon.  Keep up the great work!!!  Edit: Discovered that the search results for stars are worse than expected. The app does not identify double stars as such. Therefore not good for double star observing :(. I'm forced to remove a star from my original rating.  Back to five stars. Too much great stuff to be so fussy.
replyContent: Hi Colin, thanks a lot for the nice review and your suggestions. I put them on my ToDo list. I am aware that these features are required for this app to become more usable for more serious amateur observers. Regarding the problem with binary stars: thanks for reporting, I'll fix that with the next update this week. Best regards Wolfgang

content: I've been using the older version of this app for nearly 3 years and love it, so yesterday saw that there was a new version and bought it. Worse mistake ever! If I'd wanted an interface like Stellarium I would have bought Stellarium. Why take away the main menu (home screen) that made it easy for you to find what you're looking for. This was such a great app, but I've wasted $8 on it. there's no easy way to see what time astro light starts, when the moon is at it's brightest like the older app. Just another developer deciding to cash in on marketing and making us pay for upgrades/other feathers.
replyContent: Hi, I changed the interface due to user requests. I am afraid that I cannot serve everybody. But: you are not the only one who would like to see the old interface in the new app, so I will add it  as an optional start menu in an upcoming update. Regards Wolfgang Zima

content: Great app. Well worth the upgrade!

I didn't expect much more than a new menu system in this new version. Boy was I wrong. Every part of this app has usability updates that just make it feel smarter to use. I feel that anyone who is critical of having to buy a new version will not be disappointed once they start to use it. I'd like to add that this developer is one of the most responsive and attentive creators on the Play Store. If this app could control my telescope, it would be the only astronomy app I need.
replyContent: Thanks a lot for the nice review! Telescope control will come later this year.

content: Keep up the good work, always happy to support your efforts!
Nice to see an update to previous version (which I also own). Would be nice to see some more satellites to select? Thanks, keep up the good work and looking forward to seeing it advance.
Previous version was quite good. This is a nice improvement. Three things I would like to turn on and off individually, Ecliptic, Celestial equator, local meridian, Many thanks, keep it up.

I have used the older Mobile Observatory 2 for years and loved it. This one looks even better, and I haven't even had a chance to try all the new stuff. There was a problem with google that the author dealt with right away. It is more than worth the full upgrade cost. Keep up the great work!
replyContent: Hi the discount already was canceled two days ago but apparently Google still lists it as discount. Sorry about this, if you like, send me your order ID and I will cancel your order.

content: Debating...on whether I get my discount do this app get 5-Starz!!!
replyContent: Hi is it still listed with a discount on Google Play? Should not be since the discount was cancelled 2 days ago. I'll check with Google. Please send me your Order ID if you want to cancel your order.

content: As expected, the new version is as excellent as the previous version was. I'm still exploring the new features, but so far it promises to be an absolute pleasure to work with and is loaded with excellent & useful information. Great work!
unable to refine the screen display to my liking as in v2. Refund requested.

I paid already for version 2, now I have to pay again to get what is a simple update. This guy is ripping off his customers. Lame explanation by calling it version “3” to make people pay twice for the same program. You've been warned. Will probably charge again for the next update by calling it version “4.” At least you're warned. Don't believe fake 5* reviews.
replyContent: Hi it's a simple update after 2 years of work. If you don't like it please send me your Order ID and I'll cancel your order

content: A fantastic update which exceeded expectations. The subscription model was more than worth the money given the developer has got to make a living and, let's face it at just over £4 a year is an absolute bargain. Now, due to complaints from whiners wanting something on the cheap the subscription model has been dropped, hopefully not at the expense of stalling development. If donations are offered in the app the developer will get my support.
replyContent: Thanks a lot for your review. I'll think about the donate button 😀. Anyway, I'll go on with improving the app...

content: Excellent app with a wealth of information. Worth every penny and the subscription. Some serious work has gone into this app. Support it's development. The new interface is different but will become familiar with use. One inconsitency, select an object from the objects menu and most of the information about the object is hidden away behind a "more..."! Be good to have all this in tabs. I think this is more important than giving beta Cardboard menu status.
replyContent: Thanks for your nice review. About the object information: perhaps you are right. This should be easier accessible. I'll think about it.

content: Absolutely splendid. I downloaded extended star catalogue. Search engine finds best HD identified stars I think. Would be nice if HIP could be used too.

⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐ 10 stars. Great job‼️ The development work behind the application is great, I do not understand the reason why people complain. Consider keeping that annual subscription, offering something else.
replyContent: Thanks for the stars 😀

content: The best planetarium program just got better with the new release. The 'Tonight's Best' feature now includes many more objects and allows you to filter by things like galaxies, nebula, etc. The lack of these extra objects was my only issue with the old version. No need for any other planetarium apps!

This is a Major upgrade to the previous version which I have been using for many years . Now it's even better! This has to be the ultimate in any astronomy app. Packed full of information and detail. Worth every penny! Well done! 👍
Definitely by far the best planetarium app on the play store. A must have for every astronomer!

I've been using the older version of MO for over five years and love it. It's the only astronomy app I use on an almost daily basis and has served me very well over the years. Five bucks for this app is a steal. I would pay twice amount.  This new version has some nice new features, but the biggest and best improvement for me is the graphic depiction of the night sky - especially during twilight. I also use Sky Safari and I can tell you, hands down, MO is by far the most realistic.  If I had to choose just one app to recommend someone - paid or free - I would recommend MO.
